                e:"Kamala Basti is one of the best places to visit in Belgaum. Located inside the Belgavi Fort complex, The Kamal Basadi was built by Birchiraja, also called Jaya Raya, an officer in the court of Kartavirya IV of Ratta dynasty in c. 1204 CE under the guidance of Jain monk Subhachandrabhattarakadeva. According to an inscription dating back to 1205 CE the temple was constructed by the architect Kartaviryadeva and yuvrajakumara mallikarjunadeva. The Kamal Basadi derives its name from the lotus carvings extending from the dome of the center roof. The lotus has 72 petals believed to represent 24 tirthankaras of past, present and future. The walls of the temple are engraved with intricate designs, borders, and sculptures."
