                e: "Located near Shahpur at Shahpur- Kalburgi Road is the Sleeping Buddha Hill. A set of around 4 hills when viewed horizontally over a distance create a silhouette of a sleeping figure projecting a sharp nose, curly hair tied like a bun and hands placed on the chest resembling Lord Buddha; hence the name Sleeping Buddha. Though the hill resembles sleeping Buddha any time of the day, the best time see would be at sunrise and sunset."
